1
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:43,230
This isn't just the home of the herdsmen

2
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:44,450
and the Mazhi people,

3
00:03:45,470 --> 00:03:46,840
but also the home of the Tibetan antelope

4
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,310
and all wild animals.

5
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,810
They can't speak.

6
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:52,920
They won't file reports to you.

7
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,150
If we do it your way

8
00:03:56,430 --> 00:03:57,120
and develop

9
00:03:57,210 --> 00:03:58,090
everywhere

10
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,360
in Mazhi,

11
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:03,180
in 100 years,

12
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,800
we will be gone,

13
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:08,130
and the Tibetan antelope and wild animals

14
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:09,060
will be gone too.

15
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:11,000
And Qinghai's sacred mountains and lakes

16
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,000
will also be gone.

17
00:04:13,180 --> 00:04:14,780
Whose home will this be then?

18
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:15,820
Everything in the Mountain Patrol

19
00:05:16,930 --> 00:05:18,450
was like a dream.

20
00:05:20,630 --> 00:05:22,270
But I don't want to wake up.

21
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:25,240
Mom said

22
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,370
in this world,

23
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:30,060
those kind-hearted,

24
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:32,220
upright people

25
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,870
don't always meet a good end.

26
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:37,540
But those people

27
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,260
only follow their conscience

28
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,060
and stubbornly do the right thing.

29
00:05:44,330 --> 00:05:46,130
Even if they are misunderstood,

30
00:05:46,860 --> 00:05:48,130
despised,

31
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,890
or hurt,

32
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,180
they never hold a grudge

33
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:56,350
and never worry about the outcome.

34
00:05:59,330 --> 00:06:00,220
Time, however,

35
00:06:01,930 --> 00:06:03,460
will sift through the chaos

36
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:05,680
and reveal results

37
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,330
as precious as gold.

38
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,480
Even if you don’t get to see it,

39
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:14,060
future generations

40
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,540
will.

41
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,570
Now, I announce

42
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,010
the official

43
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,750
establishment of the

44
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:33,159
Bolamula National Nature Reserve!

45
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:20,980
You...

46
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:25,410
You are back?

47
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:29,500
I'm back.

48
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:34,800
I won't leave again.

49
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,810
I'm never leaving again.

50
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:45,720
After

51
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:47,990
the Bolamula Nature Reserve was built,

52
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,770
7 provincial and national  reserves

53
00:10:49,770 --> 00:10:50,670
were set up

54
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:52,500
across Qinghai,

55
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:55,570
including Sanjiangyuan Nature Reserve,

56
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:58,350
Golmud Populus Forest Nature Reserve,

57
00:10:58,410 --> 00:10:59,670
the Keluke Lake Nature Reserve,

58
00:10:59,670 --> 00:11:02,670
and Tuosu Lake Nature Reserve.

59
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:06,510
Altogether, there are eleven reserves,

60
00:11:07,130 --> 00:11:07,820
covering

61
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:11,270
21.77 million hectares,

62
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:14,240
with annual environmental funding

63
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:15,530
reaching billions.

64
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,220
Countless environmental volunteers,

65
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:20,270
alongside the Party and the government,

66
00:11:20,270 --> 00:11:22,510
work together to protect this Sanjiangyuan region,

67
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:24,790
known as

68
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:26,440
the "Water Tower of China."

69
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:29,820
My family also moved from Mazhi County

70
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:31,720
to Tianduo.

71
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:33,530
My family gradually got used to

72
00:11:33,530 --> 00:11:34,630
city life

73
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,050
and all found new careers.

74
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:39,030
In recent years,

75
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:42,370
Tianduo has been vigorously developing its coal industry.

76
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:43,370
Around the city,

77
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,810
7 coal mines were built one after another.

78
00:11:46,370 --> 00:11:48,600
As slag heaps grow

79
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:51,120
and the streets grow busier,

80
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:53,120
the conflict between resource development

81
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,980
and environmental protection

82
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,100
becomes clear once again.

83
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:00,670
Captain Bai! Captain Bai!

84
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:01,270
Do you guys

85
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,290
Do you need backup?

86
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,350
Do you need backup?

87
00:12:04,220 --> 00:12:04,860
No backup needed!

88
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:05,600
No backup needed!

89
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,440
The Deputy Captain and I

90
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,240
can handle it!

91
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:08,790
Alright! Alright!

92
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:09,650
Stop fighting!

93
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:10,010
Stop fighting!

94
00:12:10,010 --> 00:12:10,340
Stop fighting!

95
00:12:10,340 --> 00:12:11,170
Alright! Alright!

96
00:12:11,170 --> 00:12:12,030
Stop fighting!

97
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:13,930
Captain Bai!

98
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:19,700
Talk this out!

99
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:21,030
No fighting!

100
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:21,550
Right!

101
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:22,750
You assaulted a police officer!

102
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:23,440
Do you know that?

103
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,840
Our captain is bleeding.

104
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:25,960
Who assaulted a police officer?

105
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,030
No one did!

106
00:12:27,130 --> 00:12:28,220
You elbowed me!

107
00:12:28,770 --> 00:12:29,440
Officer.

108
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,120
Look at this.

109
00:12:31,220 --> 00:12:31,870
I was really

110
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:32,430
hit by this lady.

111
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:33,050
My face was ruined.

112
00:12:33,050 --> 00:12:34,790
He haggled with me for ages.

113
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,270
One sheep is a thousand,

114
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:37,910
and he tried to cut the price in half.

115
00:12:37,910 --> 00:12:39,860
I said I couldn't sell it like that.

116
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,130
In the end we agreed

117
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,620
on 1,500 yuan

118
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,030
for two sheep.

119
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,960
Then he suddenly said he didn’t want them anymore.

120
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,490
Alright.

121
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,030
Calm down.

122
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:48,000
It's a free market.

123
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,960
Can't I just ask?

124
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:50,400
Look at these sheep.

125
00:12:50,860 --> 00:12:51,720
The more I looked at them, the more disgusting they seemed.

126
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,100
You can’t eat them at all.

127
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:54,440
So I didn't want them anymore.

128
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,120
It is a free market,

129
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:56,780
but you have to keep your word.

130
00:12:57,370 --> 00:12:57,980
You didn’t want them,

131
00:12:57,980 --> 00:12:59,370
yet you bargained for so long.

132
00:12:59,370 --> 00:12:59,890
The price you offered

133
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:00,320
was accepted by this lady

134
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,270
in the end,

135
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,930
and then you backed out.

136
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:04,220
You're a grown man.

137
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:06,210
You can't go back on your word.

138
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:07,860
That said,

139
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:09,390
no matter the reason,

140
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:10,590
you can't hit people.

141
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:12,340
Ma'am,

142
00:13:12,940 --> 00:13:13,270
from now on,

143
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:14,200
no matter what happens,

144
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,260
talk it out calmly.

145
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:16,440
If there’s any dispute,

146
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,460
call 110

147
00:13:17,550 --> 00:13:19,120
or find the market manager.

148
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:21,510
These things are easy to resolve.

149
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,080
Don't get physical again.

150
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:23,720
Got it?

151
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:26,820
Officer.

152
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,750
Why don't you take the call first?

153
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:30,150
Yes.

154
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:31,340
You go ahead.

155
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,050
When you come back,

156
00:13:32,050 --> 00:13:33,010
we’ll continue arguing.

157
00:13:33,010 --> 00:13:33,770
Arguing?

158
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:34,690
Stop arguing!

159
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:36,280
The police are right here.

160
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:39,050
Don't move.

161
00:13:39,940 --> 00:13:40,860
Excuse me.

162
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:44,910
Mr. Bai,

163
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:46,330
any instructions?

164
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,890
My dear sister,

165
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:50,050
it’s nearly impossible

166
00:13:50,050 --> 00:13:51,700
to get through to you.

167
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:52,510
Yeah.

168
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:54,550
My phone hasn’t been working well lately.

169
00:13:54,550 --> 00:13:55,950
Buy me a new one, will you?

170
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:56,740
Stop it.

171
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,860
3:00 this afternoon—

172
00:13:57,860 --> 00:13:58,790
be there on time.

173
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,010
We’ll have

174
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,670
the moving company’s truck haul the big stuff.

175
00:14:01,670 --> 00:14:02,890
We'll use our two cars

176
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,060
for the valuables.

177
00:14:04,130 --> 00:14:06,120
Mom doesn’t have any valuables anyway.

178
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:06,840
Those old things of hers

179
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:07,580
have been used for years.

180
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:07,890
Mr. Bai.

181
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:08,940
They should’ve been thrown away long ago.

182
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:10,200
But she can’t bear to part with them.

183
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,000
What can we do?

184
00:14:11,050 --> 00:14:12,120
Be home on time.

185
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,250
Don't dawdle until dark.

186
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:13,510
Mr. Bai.

187
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,110
You got it?

188
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,970
Or Mom will be upset.

189
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:17,350
Okay, I got it.

190
00:14:17,410 --> 00:14:18,580
I'll bring you a sheep.

191
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:18,910
Okay.

192
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:20,710
I'll get to work now.

193
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:21,390
Bye.

194
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:27,810
We arrived?

195
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,800
Why did you stop here?

196
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,540
You were snoring too loud.

197
00:15:35,740 --> 00:15:36,270
Captain,

198
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,570
let me drive for a while.

199
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,700
Just go back to sleep.

200
00:16:49,960 --> 00:16:50,490
Mr. Shao.

201
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,800
Here's a summary of recent inspections

202
00:16:57,860 --> 00:16:59,130
of coal mines in several cities sent by

203
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:00,670
the Provincial Environmental Bureau.

204
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:01,740
Pick out the key points,

205
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:02,250
print them out,

206
00:17:02,250 --> 00:17:03,510
and put them on my desk.

207
00:17:05,109 --> 00:17:07,140
Print them out and put them on your desk?

208
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:08,180
You’re an investigative reporter

209
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:08,810
who covers environmental issues,

210
00:17:08,810 --> 00:17:11,270
and you don’t know about paperless offices?

211
00:17:13,109 --> 00:17:15,089
Yes, you’re right.

212
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:15,680
How about this?

213
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:16,810
After you organize it,

214
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:18,400
email it to me, okay?

215
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:22,160
You.

216
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,660
You really should start training some new people.

217
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:24,260
Don’t dump

218
00:17:24,290 --> 00:17:25,220
every task on me.

219
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:30,570
What's wrong?

220
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,290
You lifted the lid

221
00:17:32,290 --> 00:17:33,240
on Tianduo,

222
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:34,480
and they even rolled out the red carpet

223
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,200
and invited you back to do follow-up reports.

224
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:36,740
Why don’t you

225
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:37,740
seem happy at all?

226
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:38,810
Don't want to go?

227
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:40,750
Do you really think

228
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:41,400
my report

229
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,630
was lifting the lid?

230
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,220
You exposed

231
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:45,350
so many small coal mines

232
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:45,940
operating illegally.

233
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:47,350
Isn’t that lifting the lid?

234
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:50,150
That's because you didn’t read my original draft.

235
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:51,850
What I exposed there

236
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:53,610
went far beyond those small coal mines.

237
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:54,180
The reality

238
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:55,250
is much worse.

239
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,200
Thanks for your hard work, sir.

240
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,050
Grab this side.

241
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:58,980
It's a bit heavy.

242
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,010
Hold the top steady.

243
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:02,000
Hold it, hold it.

244
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:02,510
You had time

245
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:03,960
to call me 3 times in a row,

246
00:18:04,070 --> 00:18:04,400
but you couldn’t

247
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,330
spare a moment to call Mom?

248
00:18:05,330 --> 00:18:06,250
Be careful.

249
00:18:06,330 --> 00:18:08,290
It's her moving day, and she's the only one late.

250
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:09,680
Mom is having a meeting at the hospital.

251
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,740
She can't get away.

252
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,880
That's definitely a lie.

253
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:13,660
Come on, Ju.

254
00:18:13,660 --> 00:18:14,160
Why would Yan lie

255
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,690
about something like that?

256
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,310
I meant Mom.

257
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:20,940
There goes your occupational hazard again.

258
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:21,460
You’re always suspecting

259
00:18:21,460 --> 00:18:22,590
everyone of lying.

260
00:18:23,510 --> 00:18:25,460
That small hospital is private.

261
00:18:25,550 --> 00:18:26,900
They value Mom

262
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,310
because she has so much clinical experience,

263
00:18:28,310 --> 00:18:29,770
so they give her a lot to do.

264
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:30,840
Put it here.

265
00:18:32,830 --> 00:18:34,590
She uses this excuse every time.

266
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:36,250
How can there be so many meetings?

267
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:37,380
She's not Uncle Lin.

268
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:39,040
She just can’t sit still.

269
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:40,810
We brought her here after she retired

270
00:18:40,810 --> 00:18:41,960
to enjoy life.

271
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,160
Who would have thought

272
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,760
that she’d find another job?

273
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,240
Loving work too much

274
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:47,160
is a kind of illness.

275
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,290
It needs treatment.

276
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:50,570
And it's hereditary.

277
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:51,830
Put it inside the room.

278
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:54,700
What's wrong?

279
00:18:54,770 --> 00:18:56,460
I just think you're impressive.

280
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:57,880
Now that you bought a house for Mom in full,

281
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,270
you sound so confident.

282
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,140
Chun chipped in too.

283
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,770
I couldn't afford it on my own.

284
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:03,900
And thanks to Yunfei

285
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,180
for bargaining with the agent.

286
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:06,010
He got the price down a lot.

287
00:19:06,010 --> 00:19:08,410
Otherwise, we wouldn't have enough money.

288
00:19:08,770 --> 00:19:09,750
Don't drop it.

289
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,000
These are all

290
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Mom's valuables.

291
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:14,090
Her most precious things.

292
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:17,030
What kind of valuables? They’re so heavy.

293
00:19:17,110 --> 00:19:17,790
Books.

294
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,330
These things

295
00:19:20,460 --> 00:19:20,980
aren't worth a few cents

296
00:19:20,980 --> 00:19:22,110
